void handleAssert (  const char *  l,
int  n,
const char *  e
) 
 

This method is called in the MC2_ASSERT-macro.

Will flush both standard error and standard out, print the current file and the line-number to standard error and exit the prgram with the abort()-method. This will also generate a core-file. The implementation of handleAssert is located in Utility.cpp.

Parameters:
l The name of the file.
n The linenumber in l.
